title: For Sale:  AR-15 Upper Receiver Group for Sale - 16" Barrel, Quad Rail, YHM Phantom Flash Hider, Charging Handle Included, NO Bolt Carrier Group
postcontent: Up for sale is an AR-15 upper receiver group I bought in the "great panic" gun-buying frenzy of 2012. I had purchased it to interchange with the heavy 20" barrel of my coyote gun, but now that I have purchased a complete 16" carbine, I am selling this unit for a great deal less than I originally paid for it.This is an AR-15 upper receiver assembly with charging handle included, sporting a 16" barrel and free-floating quad rail. It includes a Yankee Hill Machine Phantom flash hider, plastic flip-up sights with a front fiber optic insert, a charging handle, and a sling swivel adapter. It DOES NOT INCLUDE A BOLT CARRIER GROUP (easily purchaseable online, starting around $80). It also does not include the camouflage rifle case used for a background in the photos. I purchased this upper receiver group off of Gunbroker from a gentleman that was assembling these himself, so I am unsure of the provenance of many of the parts. I can tell you that the flash hider is a YHM Phantom unit, the barrel is marked "1/7 5.56 NATO", and the upper receiver has the keyhole forging mark of Cerro Forge, a reputable forging company that also does Colt upper receiver groups. I have fired about 50 rounds through this unit and it performed reliably without stoppages, and the backup sights are zeroed at about 50 yards. Note that this is not a premium upper receiver, but it is fully functional and should make a great building block for a first-time AR-15, a knockaround range gun, or a backup upper receiver for a rifle in a different configuration. I'd like to request serious, in-state buyers only, and will ask to take a look at your driver's license before performing the transaction, just to ensure that you are a well-intentioned buyer from a state that permits these kinds of things.
